data.title: expensive and no imagination
data.text: way too expensive and a boring selection. The staff is nice, but they make no exceptions fro people who can't afford their high prices. I have not been ther in several years because I am not made of money.

data.title: Good options, but a little slow
data.text: I visited the cafe/grill because of a rush for time. While the wait was long I thought the food was fine. The staff I interacted with were relatively friendly. I ordered a black bean burger and was surprised to find it was made in house. They also have a salad bar which was a good side option if you don't want fries. They do charge for water cups though. Honestly, I thought they were doing a pretty good job and for prices at a location with a captive audience they are pretty fair.

data.title: Pricey!
data.text: For what you get, it is very pricey.  Also, they seem to be out of food items all of the time.  The cashier is a little rude also.  If I could go out somewhere else to eat, I would.  Waste of money.
